-- Saudi Arabia Cement Makers to Work at Capacity, Eqtisadiah Says
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-02-04T08:24:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/saudi-arabia-cement-makers-to-work-at-capacity-eqtisadiah-says.html
Saudi Arabia  will require cement
producers to operate at full capacity to help end a supply
shortage in the local market,  Al-Eqtisadiah  reported, citing an
unidentified person at the Ministry of Commerce.  A new plant in the western region will start operations in
a few days to supply the area with 5,000 tons a day, the
newspaper said, citing the person.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
